Adult.description: Wilson's Snipes have longer legs than American Woodcocks. They also have barring on the flanks and a white belly, while American Woodcocks have clean flanks and a cinnamon belly.
Killdeer have a very different shape from woodcock, with a short bill, slender body, upright posture, and longer legs. They have clean white underparts and 2 black bands across the breast.
